article.headline: Jacksonville St. 80, Tenn.-Martin 68
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- Nick Murphy scored 18 points and grabbed 13 rebounds and Trenton Marshall chipped in 20 points to lead Jacksonville State past Tennessee-Martin 80-68 on Thursday night. The Gamecocks (11-13, 7-7 Ohio Valley Conference) scored 19 points off 17 turnovers, and had 16 fastbreak points. Jacksonville State had 17 assists and shot 46.2 percent from the field (24 of 52). The Gamecocks led by as many as 45-26 on Amadou Mbodji's free throws with 15:52 to play. Jeremy Bynum added 12 points for Jacksonville State, which snapped a two-game losing streak. Marquis Weddle paced the Skyhawks (4-20, 1-13) with 17 points. Tennessee-Martin's Andres Irarrazabal and Benzor Simmons added 12 points each. The Skyhawks shot 39.7 percent from the field (23 of 58) and were 4 of 12 from 3-point range (33.3 percent).
